column1: Table 30--Indexes of feed consuming animal units (millions)

1/ Index is based on the dry-weight quantity of feed consumed by the average milk cow during marketing years 1969/70-71/72. Market year is September-August. Latest data may be preliminary or projected.

Source: Calculated by USDA, Economic Research Service from animal inventory numbers published by USDA, National Agricultural Statistics Service in Cattle; Sheep and Goats; Hogs and Pigs; Chickens and Eggs; and Turkeys Raised; and from horse and mule inventory numbers published in the Census of Agriculture.
